sub_title: Student of Msc biology / Junior applied biologist
summary: I am an energetic person who loves finding places where different fields overlap (for instance, biology, and technology). In the future, I plan to combine this with my passion for wildlife conservation by finding new and innovative solutions. I love traveling and being outdoors. In my future job, I want to keep learning new skills and grow as a person, I prefer working in teams but I also work well on my own. Working as a farmhand, and during my research internship in South Africa, I gained experience working with animals and basic knowledge about craftsmanship. I have a Bachelor's degree in Applied Science - BASc focused in Biology, General from HAS University of Applied Sciences. Through my history of projects and internships, I have a lot of experience in medical laboratory research and ecological research. I am currently in the second year of my master's in Biology at Wageningen University, here I am combining my passion for biology and technology by selecting subjects in the fields of ecology and data science.

projects: [{'title': 'The use of pesticides on grass sports fields in the province of Noord-Brabant (Netherlands)', 'date': {'start': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}, 'end': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}}, 'description': "At the start of 2020 the use of pesticides on grass sports fields wasn't allowed anymore, except for specific cases where no other solution can be found. And by the 31th of december 2022 these exceptions will not be made anymore. Because of these new regulations most provinces are working towards pesticide free maintenance of grass sports fields within their province. But because a lot of sports clubs are private, the gathering of data on how much pesticides are being used is complicated. During this project me and my project partner (Kim Kleeven) tried to gather as much information on how far clubs in Noord-Brabant were in achieving full pesticide free maintenance of the grass fields. These results were then presented at the province-tour 2020 in Noord-Brabant.  This project was done in association with the province of Noord-Brabant and BSNC.", 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Cassander', 'last_name': 'Engelen', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Student of Msc biology / Junior applied biologist'}]}]
